                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On another slab built into the floor of the first <hi rend="italic">prakāra</hi>, north of the central shrine in the Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Achyutappa-Nāyaka. 1564 A.D. (?)</p>						
                            
                            <p>The inscription is dated in Ś. 1482, Rudhirōdgārin Paṅguni 29. The śaka and the cyclic years do not tally. Rudhirōdgārin falls in Śaka 1485.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This seems to record the grant of income from levies such as <hi rend="italic">araimaṉai śōḍi, adhikāri [kaḍaikkūṭṭu]</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">śōḍi-puṟavagai</hi>, as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi>, for the merit of his father Śevvappa Nāyaka of Neḍuṅguṉṟam by Achyutappa Nāyaka. Other details are lost as the inscription is damaged.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
